1. *Firmi* je potreban novi menadžer. (The company needs a new manager.)
2. Ova *firmi* se bavi proizvodnjom automobila. (This company is engaged in the production of cars.)
3. Radnici ove *firme* su organizovali štrajk. (The workers of this company organized a strike.)
4. *Firme* u ovom sektoru se suočavaju sa velikim izazovima. (Companies in this sector are facing great challenges.)
5. Menadžeri ove *firme* često putuju u inostranstvo. (The managers of this company often travel abroad.)
6. Kupovina akcija ove *firme* može biti isplativa investicija. (Buying shares of this company can be a profitable investment.)
7. Nije lako voditi *firmu* u današnje vreme. (It's not easy to run a company in today's world.)
8. Ova *firma* je postigla značajan uspeh na tržištu. (This company has achieved significant success in the market.)
9. Radim u *firmi* koja se bavi proizvodnjom odeće. (I work in a company that produces clothing.)
10. *Firma* koja ne prati trendove na tržištu, teško može opstati. (A company that does not follow market trends is difficult to survive.)

Note: The Serbian word "firmi" is the genitive or dative case singular form of the word "firma", which means "company" in English.